## PHASE 11: Intelligence Metadata + Feedback UI ⭐ (NEW)

> **This is the unique part — not in the original TraceRoot UI. This surfaces your KAN pipeline intelligence and collects feedback for Stage 9.**

### 11.1 Intelligence Metadata Display

On every assistant message, show metadata from `ChatbotResponse.metadata`:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🤖 Assistant                                    │
│                                                 │
│ [HIGH ✅] [N+1 Query] [⚡ Fast Path] [234ms]    │  ← metadata bar
│                                                 │
│ "The checkout endpoint has an N+1 query          │
│  pattern in get_user_cart [1]..."                │
│                                                 │
│                            [👍] [👎]             │  ← feedback buttons
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Metadata bar elements:**
| Element | Source | Display |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Confidence badge | `metadata.confidence` | HIGH=green pill, MEDIUM=yellow pill, LOW=red pill |
| Pattern tag | `metadata.pattern_matched` | Blue outline pill: "N+1 Query", "Slow Query", etc. |
| Fast path indicator | `metadata.fast_path` | ⚡ lightning bolt if true, 🧠 brain if full LLM |
| Processing time | `metadata.processing_time_ms` | Gray text: "234ms" |
| Causes count | `metadata.causes_found` | If > 1: "3 causes found" |

### 11.2 Feedback Buttons (👍 / 👎)

On every assistant message with `message_type === "assistant"`:

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-1 mt-1">
  <Button variant="ghost" size="sm" onClick={() => submitFeedback("positive")}>
    👍
  </Button>
  <Button variant="ghost" size="sm" onClick={() => submitFeedback("negative")}>
    👎
  </Button>
</div>
```

### 11.3 Feedback API

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/feedback/route.ts`
- POST: Proxies to Python backend → updates [intelligence_metrics](file:///c:/traceroot-main/src/dao/sqlite_dao.py#538-613) record
- Body: `{ chat_id, message_timestamp, feedback: "positive" | "negative" }`
- Backend calls `dao.update_user_feedback(chat_id, timestamp, feedback)`

> **This feedback is consumed by Stage 9 (Evaluator)** in the weekly evaluation loop. The evaluator reads [intelligence_metrics](file:///c:/traceroot-main/src/dao/sqlite_dao.py#538-613) records with feedback, calculates pattern accuracy, and adjusts `eval_config.json`.

### 11.4 Backend Changes Needed

Add one new endpoint to [ChatRouterClass](file:///c:/traceroot-main/rest/routers/chat.py#30-323):

```python
# rest/routers/chat.py
self.router.post("/update-feedback")(self.update_feedback)

async def update_feedback(self, request: Request, req_data: FeedbackRequest):
    """Update user feedback for an intelligence metrics record."""
    result = await self.driver.update_feedback(
        chat_id=req_data.chat_id,
        message_timestamp=req_data.message_timestamp,
        feedback=req_data.feedback,
    )
    return result
```

