## How the UI Connects to Your KAN Pipeline Stages

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        YOUR UI                               │
│                                                              │
│  User types question ──► POST /api/chat                      │
│                              │                               │
│                    ┌─────────▼──────────┐                    │
│                    │  Python Backend     │                    │
│                    │                     │                    │
│                    │  Stage 1: Ingest    │                    │
│                    │  Stage 2: Tree      │                    │
│                    │  Stage 3: Intel     │ ← pattern_matched │
│                    │  Stage 4: Router    │ ← fast_path       │
│                    │  Stage 5: LLM       │                   │
│                    │  Stage 6: Validate  │                   │
│                    │  Stage 7: Persist   │ ← stores metrics  │
│                    │  Stage 8: Respond   │ ← metadata        │
│                    └─────────┬──────────┘                    │
│                              │                               │
│  ChatbotResponse ◄───────────┘                               │
│  ├── message (markdown with [1] refs)                        │
│  ├── references[] (span links)                               │
│  └── metadata (confidence, pattern, fast_path, timing)       │
│                                                              │
│  UI renders: message + metadata bar + feedback buttons       │
│                                                              │
│  User clicks 👍/👎 ──► POST /api/feedback                   │
│                              │                               │
│                    ┌─────────▼──────────┐                    │
│                    │  Stage 9: Evaluator │ ← reads feedback  │
│                    │  (weekly cron job)  │ ← adjusts weights │
│                    │  Writes eval_config │ ← improves Stage 3│
│                    └────────────────────┘                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

---

## Build Order Recommendation

Start with Phases 1-2 (setup + auth), then **Phase 3-4** (settings + integrate) because they're simpler and let you test MongoDB connections. Then **Phase 5** (trace list) — this is the hardest, most code-intensive phase. Once the trace list works, Phases 6-12 layer on incrementally.

**Phase 11** (intelligence metadata + feedback) is the most important differentiator — it's what makes this UI different from Grafana's. Don't skip it.
